  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency drought response through provision of temporary clean safe water, hygiene promotion, sanitation and health care services</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Receiving a total of US$ 1.7 million from CERF for the implementation of lifesaving activities, IOM will use $1 million to provide clean drinking water through five weeks of water trucking to 36,000 people (3780 m3). In addition, IOM will provide hygiene kits (including menstrual hygiene management items) and hygiene messaging to the same people. 36,000 Somalis will be reached by the WASH component of this project, including 7,200 women and 12,600 girls. The remaining $700,000 will be used by IOM to provide primary health-care services through 11 static health facilities and mobile outreach teams that will conduct 79,196 outpatient consultations and vaccinate 10,135 children. In total, 89,331 Somalis will be reached by the health component of this project, including 24,907 women and 20,652 girls.</narrative>
  </description>
